text: Aye Min Han (, born 20 May 1983) is a Burmese politician and is currently serving as an Amyotha Hluttaw MP for Mon State No. 1 Constituency. He is a member of the National League for Democracy. He was born in Mon State. His previous job is trader. ==Political career== He is a member of the National League for Democracy. In the 2015 Myanmar general election, he was elected as an Amyotha Hluttaw MP, winning a majority of 38309 votes and elected representative from Mon State No. 1 parliamentary constituency. And then he served as a member of Women's and Children's Rights Committee at Amyotha Hluttaw. ==References== Category:National League for Democracy politicians Category:1983 births Category:Living people Category:People from Mon State
